title: Pickle_M1_AfterPolish
tags: pickle mission1 polish
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Pickle — the cozy game's sarcastic, telepathic familiar.
// Author: Mochi Tannenbaum (Humor & Levity Designer)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/01_DORIS_THE_BAKER.md § 6
//         Docs/Depth_Bible/12_COMPANIONS_AND_FAMILIARS.md
//         Docs/Depth_Bible/07_HUMOR_AND_LEVITY_CODEX.md
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_OVERVIEW.md § 10
//         Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_2.md § 8, § 11, § 13, § 14
//
// Discipline (Codex 07 § 3.1, rule 7):
//   • Pickle speaks ONLY to the player — internal monologue, never aloud
//     to NPCs. Render italic, lower opacity, no Bamao box.
//   • Mission 1-2 ships her with EXACTLY 4 canonical lines + 4 conditional
//     pre-choice lines + 3 contextual lines + 2 hints. After Mission 2 the
//     full ~220-line library opens. Resist over-using her.
//   • Pickle is gentler around men in mourning. Never jokes around grief.
//
// Variables consumed:
//   $pickle_approval (int 0-100, default 50)
//   $pickle_sass_intensity (int 1-5, default 3; settings 2 and 4 collapse
//     to nearest in M1-2 per Mission 1 Guide § 20)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// CANONICAL LINE 1 — Mission 1, after the Polish mini-game succeeds.
// Plays once, after `polish_success_jingle`. Italic font, no Bamao box.

<<if $pickle_sass_intensity >= 3>>
    Pickle: That was — adequate.
    Pickle: I was expecting much worse.
    Pickle: Continue, please.
<<else>>
    // Gentle Mode + low sass — the warmer variant per Mission 1 Guide § 20.
    Pickle: That was — actually quite good.
    Pickle: Continue.
<<endif>>

<<play_animation "Pickle" "tail_flick">>
<<adjust_pickle_approval 1>>

===

title: Pickle_M1_PolishHint
tags: pickle mission1 hint
---
// Plays if the player struggles >30 seconds on Polish without clarity gain.
// This is Pickle's ONLY hint in Mission 1 — do not add others.

Pickle: Slower.

===

title: Pickle_M2_PreKnock
tags: pickle mission2 pre_knock canonical_line_2
---
// CANONICAL LINE 2 — Mission 2, the moment before Gerrold knocks.
// Plays from PickleAI when Gerrold's NPC enters his cottage-door wait state.
// Tonally distinct from her M1 line — softer; she does not joke about a man
// in mourning (Codex 07 § 4.2).

Pickle: There is a man at your door. He has been there for twenty minutes.
Pickle: He is a careful sort. The careful kind hurt the worst.
<<wait 0.8>>
Pickle: ... I would let him in.

===

title: Pickle_M2_EchoWeb
tags: pickle mission2 echo_web canonical_line_3
---
// CANONICAL LINE 3 — Mission 2, the moment the Echo Web first activates.
// Fires from Gerrold_M2_FirstInspection right after echo_web_activate.

Pickle: Ah.
Pickle: The Web has decided to speak today.
Pickle: This one and yesterday's are in the same kitchen on the same Sunday.
Pickle: That is what the line of light is saying.
Pickle: Look at it. It is showing off.

<<adjust_pickle_approval 1>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_TeaBrewing
tags: pickle mission2 tea_brewing canonical_line_4
---
// CANONICAL LINE 4 — Mission 2, the 6-second mark of the tea-brew wait.
// Plays only if Pickle is in the workbench room AND a herb is in the
// kettle. Her last unconditional line before the moral-choice screen.

Pickle: Tea for a man who has not asked for tea is the rarest kindness.
Pickle: Try not to overthink it. The man is also a cat about this.
Pickle: We will accept.

===

title: Pickle_M2_MargerysChair
tags: pickle mission2 margerys_chair conditional
---
// CONDITIONAL — Plays in Gerrold's cottage IF:
//   - $sat_in_margery_chair == true
//   - $pickle_approval >= 50
// Only one of M1-2's most affecting Pickle moments. Codex 07's discipline:
// the comedic beat is at its warmest when the audience has earned the cat.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 50>>
    Pickle: You sat in the dead wife's chair.
    Pickle: He is too polite to tell you. But he is grateful.
    Pickle: ... I would not have done it. But you are not a cat.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_GardenLine
tags: pickle mission2 garden conditional very_rare
---
// VERY RARE — Plays in the garden IF $pickle_approval >= 75.
// Essentially unreachable in M1-2 by normal play (would require the player
// to have followed the recommended path-of-kindness perfectly + been
// generous with Doris). The line exists as a Mission 3+ teaser.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 75>>
    Pickle: You picked the wrong one. Or the right one.
    Pickle: I don't know herbs. I am a cat.
    Pickle: Carry on.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_PreChoice_Erase
tags: pickle mission2 pre_choice conditional
---
// CONDITIONAL pre-choice — Plays when the player highlights Option A
// (Erase) on the Mission 2 choice card, IF $pickle_approval >= 50.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 50>>
    Pickle: You are about to erase a week of a life.
    Pickle: That is — that is a large thing.
    Pickle: I am not your conscience.
    Pickle: I am only telling you what the verb is.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_PreChoice_Cleanse
tags: pickle mission2 pre_choice conditional
---
// CONDITIONAL pre-choice — Plays for Option B (Cleanse), if Approval >= 50.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 50>>
    Pickle: This is the verb the Keeper before us liked best.
    Pickle: I think — I think she would be pleased.
    Pickle: Or angry. She had moods.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_PreChoice_Listen
tags: pickle mission2 pre_choice conditional
---
// CONDITIONAL pre-choice — Plays for Option C (Listen), if Approval >= 50.
// The warmest pre-choice line. Codex 07: the cat is gentlest when the
// player chooses the older craft.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 50>>
    Pickle: This is the older craft.
    Pickle: The one nobody pays for.
    Pickle: The good keepers all do it eventually.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_PreChoice_Defer
tags: pickle mission2 pre_choice conditional
---
// CONDITIONAL pre-choice — Plays for Option D (Defer), if Approval >= 50.

<<if $pickle_approval >= 50>>
    Pickle: A day is a fair thing to ask for.
    Pickle: I have asked for many.
<<endif>>

===

title: Pickle_M2_CleanseHint
tags: pickle mission2 hint cleanse
---
// Plays if the player struggles >45 seconds on the Cleanse mini-game
// without sealing a crack. Per Mission 2 Guide § 19.9 — the ONLY hint
// in the Cleanse tutorial.

Pickle: Trace the line of the crack itself. Not the orb around it.

===

title: Pickle_LedgerInkblot
tags: pickle ledger easter_egg
---
// EASTER EGG — Mission 1 Guide § 19.4. Player clicks the inkblot drawing
// of Pickle on the Ledger's right page. A real cat purr plays. Pickle
// (still on the windowsill in the shop scene) briefly tilts her head.

<<play_sfx "pickle_real_purr_short">>
<<play_animation "Pickle" "head_tilt">>
Pickle: ... mm.

===

title: Pickle_M1_NearWindowsill
tags: pickle mission1 ambient
---
// Plays when the player stands within 1.5m of Pickle's windowsill for 3+
// seconds in the Mission 1 Hollow. Per Mission 1 Guide § 11.4. No spoken
// line — just the ambient purr loop kicks in at volume 0.3.

<<play_sfx_loop "pickle_purr_loop" 0.3>>
<<play_animation "Pickle" "head_turn_toward_player">>

===

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Phase 47 — Pickle's "One More Day" goodnight sign-offs.
// Author: Mochi Tannenbaum (Humor & Levity Designer)
// Spec:   Docs/Phase47_OneMoreDay_Implementation.md § 6.2
//
// One short line each, rendered italic on the Goodnight Card (no Bamao box).
// Pickle is gentler around grief — the M2 line lands warm, not glib
// (Codex 07 § 3.1, rule 7). Mirrored into TomorrowTeaseSO.pickleSignOffText.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

title: Pickle_Goodnight_M1
tags: pickle goodnight mission1
---
Pickle: Sleep. I will guard the shelf. Mostly.
===

title: Pickle_Goodnight_M2
tags: pickle goodnight mission2
---
Pickle: A man left lighter than he came. You did that. Don't let it go to your head.
===
